<p><strong>How can I apply these strategies to my own nursing practice?</strong></p>
<p>By understanding the strategies for theory construction, nurses can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Enhance their understanding of nursing phenomena and patient outcomes.</li>
<li>Critically evaluate existing theories and contribute to the development of new ones.</li>
<li>Design and implement research studies to test and refine theories.</li>
<li>Use theories to guide nursing practice and improve patient care.</li>
</ul>